r"""
MAIL-CHAIN SUMMARIZER (MSG + PDFs + PNG/JPG) — Notebook-safe, Python 3.14
========================================================================

What it does
- Recursively scans these folders:
  1) ...\Available data\Mails
  2) ...\Available data\Mails Rasmus
  3) ...\Available data\Mails Birgit
- For each .msg:
  - Extracts Subject + Body (tries to split the chain into messages)
  - Re-orders so the OLDEST message is treated as the “first message” (bottom of chain)
  - Extracts text from attached PDFs (either embedded in .msg OR nearby exported PDFs in folders)
  - Extracts image text/meaning from attached images:
      Option A (recommended): Vision LLM (if you have a vision deployment)
      Option B (fallback): OCR via pytesseract (only if you have it installed & working)

- Then creates ONE combined summary of ALL conversations:
  - <= 2500 words (hard cap enforced)
  - Bullet points + headings
  - Includes: recurring questions, decisions/answers, requirements, open points, owners (if present), deadlines (if present)

Dependencies
- pip install --user extract-msg openai
- Optional: pip install --user pdfplumber pypdf pillow pytesseract

IMPORTANT NOTES
- If you do NOT have a vision-capable deployment name, leave VISION_DEPLOYMENT=None.
- If you do have a vision deployment, set VISION_DEPLOYMENT to that deployment name.

Outputs
- Writes a markdown summary file to OUTPUT_DIR, plus a small JSON stats file.
"""

